The default values for the rate limiter (30, 10, 5) are hardcoded here. For better maintainability and clarity, consider defining these as exported constants in the `agent` package (e.g., in `ratelimit.go`).

For example, in `internal/agent/ratelimit.go`:
```go
const (
    DefaultMaxCallsPerMinute  = 30
    DefaultMaxCallsPerRequest = 10
    DefaultMaxDestructive     = 5
)
```

Then you can use them here:
```go
maxPerMin, maxPerReq, maxDestructive := agent.DefaultMaxCallsPerMinute, agent.DefaultMaxCallsPerRequest, agent.DefaultMaxDestructive
```
